<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="68" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1518,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
This species is distributed from the Iberian peninsula across central and southern Europe, 
<collectingCountry box="[1162,1239,1554,1580]" name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Russia</collectingCountry>
, Crimea and 
<collectingCountry name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G." box="[252,492,1590,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10290" refString="Naumann, C. M., Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G. (1999) The western Palaearctic Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo, Stenstrup, 304 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Naumann 
<emphasis box="[370,426,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
). As was stated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sasic, M. &amp; Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M." box="[704,909,1590,1619]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref10538" refString="Sasic, M., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. (2016) Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera) in the Lepidoptera collections of the Croatian Natu- ral History Museum. Natura Croatica, 25, 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2016.25.19" type="journal article" year="2016">
Šašić 
<emphasis box="[770,818,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, historical records of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1313,1395,1590,1616]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
are rather scarce. The only exact locality, Bosiljevo, was given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sasic, M. &amp; Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M." box="[890,1094,1626,1655]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref10538" refString="Sasic, M., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. (2016) Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera) in the Lepidoptera collections of the Croatian Natu- ral History Museum. Natura Croatica, 25, 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2016.25.19" type="journal article" year="2016">
Šašić 
<emphasis box="[955,1003,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rebel, H." box="[1104,1250,1626,1652]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="97 - 377" refId="ref10440" refString="Rebel, H. (1904) Studien uber die Lepidopterenfauna der Balkanlander. II. Teil. Bosnien und Herzegowina. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 19, 97 - 377." type="journal article" year="1904">Rebel (1904)</bibRefCitation>
mentions it only for Dalmatia, a larger coastal region of 
<collectingCountry box="[633,718,1662,1688]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Stauder, H." box="[797,963,1662,1688]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref10678" refString="Stauder, H. (1921) Die Zygaenidenarmut der adriatischen Inseln. Societas entomologica, 36, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1921">Stauder (1921)</bibRefCitation>
mentions it from the coastal areas of 
<collectingRegion box="[1379,1437,1662,1688]" country="Croatia" name="Istarska" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Istria</collectingRegion>
and Dalmatia. During this survey the species was recorded on three localities with eight collected specimens (
<figureCitation box="[206,274,1734,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,189,1860]" captionTargetId="figure-28@12.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution of Adscita geryon in Croatia based on newly collected data and historical records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4643399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4643399/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). These are the first recent records of 
<taxonomicName authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[698,807,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geryon">
<emphasis box="[698,807,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">A. geryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[842,924,1734,1760]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
after almost a century (
<bibRefCitation author="Stauder, H." box="[1188,1340,1734,1760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref10678" refString="Stauder, H. (1921) Die Zygaenidenarmut der adriatischen Inseln. Societas entomologica, 36, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1921">Stauder 1921</bibRefCitation>
) and the first ones with precise localities and collection dates. All three localities (two of them being very close one to another) are located within Lička Plješevica montane range at the border with 
<collectingCountry box="[1087,1349,1806,1832]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Bosnia &amp; Herzegovina</collectingCountry>
. This is a very diverse area in terms of butterfly diversity (
<bibRefCitation author="Koren, T. &amp; Laus, B. &amp; Tvrtkovic, N. &amp; Verovnik, R." box="[771,974,1842,1868]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="257 - 283" refId="ref9697" refString="Koren, T., Laus, B., Tvrtkovic, N. &amp; Verovnik, R. (2020) Butterfly diversity of Licka Pljesevica Mountain chain, Croatia (Lepi- doptera: Papilionoidea). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia, 48, 257 - 283." type="journal article" year="2020">
Koren 
<emphasis box="[851,908,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
) and seemingly also for the 
<taxonomicName box="[1299,1433,1842,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Zygaenidae</taxonomicName>
. This is a significant expanse of the known range in 
<collectingCountry box="[773,855,1878,1904]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
as the record from Bosiljevo is distanced about 
<quantity metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" unit="km" value="140.0">140 km</quantity>
from Mt. Lička Plješevica. The discovered populations in 
<collectingCountry box="[912,994,1914,1940]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
are probably connected to the ones in 
<collectingCountry box="[198,461,1950,1976]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Bosnia &amp; Herzegovina</collectingCountry>
. However, recent surveys on the 
<taxonomicName box="[839,970,1950,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Zygaenidae</taxonomicName>
of the country are lacking so this cannot be proven.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="69" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" box="[151,269,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geryion">
<emphasis box="[151,269,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">A. geryion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also known from 
<collectingCountry box="[501,777,151,177]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Bosnia and Herzegovina</collectingCountry>
from where 
<taxonomicName authority="(Alberti, 1938)" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Alberti" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[923,1331,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="geryion" subSpecies="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[923,1154,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">A. geryion orientalis</emphasis>
(Alberti, 1938)
</taxonomicName>
has been described and the specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[588,670,187,213]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Croatia</collectingCountry>
most probably belong to this subspecies. Such records have already been hypothesized in the recent work (
<bibRefCitation author="Sasic, M. &amp; Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M." box="[633,830,223,251]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref10538" refString="Sasic, M., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. (2016) Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera) in the Lepidoptera collections of the Croatian Natu- ral History Museum. Natura Croatica, 25, 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2016.25.19" type="journal article" year="2016">
Šašić 
<emphasis box="[701,751,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">et al</emphasis>
., 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) when it was stated that 
<taxonomicName authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Alberti" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[1110,1342,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="geryion" subSpecies="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[1110,1342,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">A. geryion orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the Bosnian Mountains (Makljen pass) but must occur in more parts of the Dinaric Alps. This has now been confirmed with this survey. Habitats on which 
<taxonomicName authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" box="[831,947,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geryion">
<emphasis box="[831,947,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">A. geryion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded are large montane grasslands, which were once used for cattle grazing but are nowadays mostly abandoned. As the species was collected in several different years, it seems that the population is present and possibly numerous. Even after this survey, 
<taxonomicName authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[198,307,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geryon">
<emphasis box="[198,307,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">A. geryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the rarest 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1828" box="[548,677,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Procridinae">Procridinae</taxonomicName>
species in 
<collectingCountry box="[801,883,403,429]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Croatia</collectingCountry>
and additional efforts should be taken in order to map its distribution and asses its conservation status. Additional surveys are needed on other high mountains of 
<collectingCountry box="[198,283,475,501]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, especially Velebit and Dinara in order to additionally explore the distribution range of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
